<LP>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. -- Kansas City Southern Industries Inc.
said it raised its tender offer for the 12.9% of DST Systems
Inc. that it doesn't already own to $15.85 a share, from $14.
   Kansas City Southern, a railroad and financial services
data-processing concern, already owns 16.6 DST million
shares.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said the offer is valued at about $39 million
for the remaining roughly 2.5 million shares of DST.
   DST is a financial services company based in Kansas City.
</TEXT>
